  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: e9620f8c34305754d8cc9a7e49e852d9, type: 3}
  m_Name: Tutorial_en
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_LocaleId:
    m_Code: en
  m_SharedData: {fileID: 11400000, guid: e00198e87a257ff41b02cc989c3a409a, type: 2}
  m_Metadata:
    m_Items:
    - rid: 2319839819189715041
  m_TableData:
  - m_Id: 11264212992
    m_Localized: Hello! Welcome to Pantory!
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
      - rid: 2319839819189715041
  - m_Id: 438890283008
    m_Localized: Pantory is a factory management simulation game.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 575934971904
    m_Localized: First, let me explain how to play the game. You can view the tutorial
      at any time by clicking the question mark button in each window.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1678642659328
    m_Localized: You can see where your capital is going with the Credits and Research
      Points buttons in the top left.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2291514359808
    m_Localized: This container displays the employment status, allocation status,
      and satisfaction level of employees.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2320476028928
    m_Localized: And this container has a time and time adjustment button, a tutorial
      button and a settings button.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2777508364288
    m_Localized: This is where the buttons for quickly switching between each important
      panel are located.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5943566155776
    m_Localized: Now let's talk about threads. It's easy to think of threads as a
      collection of factories.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 7203816095744
    m_Localized: When you create a thread, it takes the amount of resources designed
      for that thread and can create resources.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 7579063697408
    m_Localized: Thread installation is possible from the corresponding panel. Simply
      create a thread, select it, and install it.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 7894026567680
    m_Localized: When creating a thread, you can also set a category for the thread.
      The thread will be classified according to that category, and you can filter
      the thread categories in this panel.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 8131256401920
    m_Localized: Resources are crucial, as your primary goal is to generate them
      and sell them on the market. You can check your current resource status on
      this panel.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 9056704413696
    m_Localized: This concludes the main panel description for Pantory. There are
      tutorials for other panels, so familiarizing yourself with them will help you
      enjoy the game. We hope you enjoy your time in Pantory! Thank you!
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 11779361357824
    m_Localized: This is the button that toggles between thread build mode and thread
      remove mode.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 12960301203456
    m_Localized: This is the storage panel. This panel shows you the inventory of
      resources you currently have.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 13340426780672
    m_Localized: Resources have categories corresponding to each resource, and you
      can filter resources by category in the resource panel.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 17836750028800
    m_Localized: This is the order panel. Each group requests resources from you,
      and you accept the requests and submit the resources.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 17928651423744
    m_Localized: Each order comes from the Market, Company, and Government, and the
      size of the order tends to increase in that order. The size of the order may
      also vary depending on your company's Wealth.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18539786682368
    m_Localized: You can filter where each order came from here.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18834268766208
    m_Localized: If you accept an order, you can view the accepted orders through
      this toggle.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 19061579071488
    m_Localized: A list of clients by client category can be found here. Clicking
      on a client will display a list of orders available to that client.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 19397370855424
    m_Localized: If an order comes in, it will be displayed here and if you click
      to accept it, it will be moved to the accepted order.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 19716532224000
    m_Localized: This is the Market Panel. Here, you can buy and sell resources and
      check out information about other competing companies.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 22018345287680
    m_Localized: Here you can choose whether to display the resource view or the
      trader (competitor) view via the button.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 22020337582080
    m_Localized: This is the Resource View. You can adjust your current resource
      purchase and sale volume here.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 24215317528576
    m_Localized: Resource information is displayed here.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 24483870425088
    m_Localized: The price history of resources is visually displayed here.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 24698149027840
    m_Localized: This is the Trader (Competitor) View. You can view information about
      each trader.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 36510642880512
    m_Localized: This is the panel where you can manage your employees.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 36904429305856
    m_Localized: This is where your current management skills are demonstrated. Employees
      require a certain number of managers per employee. Depending on how many managers
      are lacking, your satisfaction level will be penalized.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 37440536854528
    m_Localized: Employees' satisfaction is affected by various variables, and you
      can find out where the influence comes from here.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 37828904239104
    m_Localized: Employee efficiency depends on their satisfaction, and this efficiency
      affects the productivity of the thread. Employees' demands also change depending
      on their satisfaction.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 38302378246144
    m_Localized: The easiest way to increase employee satisfaction is to pay them
      more. And the opposite is also true.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 39086448852992
    m_Localized: Employees are divided into Workers, Technicians, Researchers, and
      Managers. Workers perform simple tasks within a thread, Technicians perform
      technical tasks within a thread, Researchers produce RP (Research Points),
      and Managers are responsible for managing employees.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 39688935456768
    m_Localized: Here, you can decide whether to hire or fire employees. Hiring or
      firing employees costs credits, and firing employees will decrease their satisfaction.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  references:
    version: 2
